<node id="EC2">
  <data key="d0">EC2</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) is a cloud computing service provided by Amazon Web Services (AWS) that enables users to run applications on virtual servers, offering resizable compute capacity in the cloud. This versatile platform supports a wide range of applications, making it a fundamental component of AWS's cloud offerings.

EC2 is employed to host various applications within different environments. For instance, it is used for hosting the DocuSeal Pro application in the orbiters_2 environment, and it serves as the deployment platform for the Django application associated with the ONZ APP. Additionally, EC2 supports the Data Keeper initiative by hosting another Django application. 

The service is also utilized for managing specific functionalities such as API deployment for applications like onzenna, and it plays a critical role in testing HTTP requests for n8n while facilitating domain routing management. Furthermore, EC2 provides features such as SSH access, which is often integral for troubleshooting and managing deployed applications. 

Overall, Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2) presents significant flexibility and scalability for deploying and managing applications, making it a key element in the infrastructure of numerous digital services and applications across various environments.&lt;SEP&gt;EC2 refers to Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud, used for hosting PostgreSQL and managing data storage.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e980f33ef75a45c4be6b30d1ae17cb57&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9c0a9988cca5a59cdf442104da4d4aad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a888095b75532d88729c62a0889cda38&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7767dba93036189c364097f1aae5f9e6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91bdba8d279e91794bda27ec40d1bbd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dd6fd8b0a9a7189ace28dcd3e06fa6c3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4dd9f3debaf9d08b8b0c408008498f0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7fa81dc7d19a7c2d0fbd95c643e718fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-611922e16f2181d18a953eed8873d5fa</data>
