<node id="Amazon Ads">
  <data key="d0">Amazon Ads</data>
  <data key="d1">datasource</data>
  <data key="d2">Amazon Ads is the advertising service provided by Amazon, designed to enable sellers and brands to promote their products both on the Amazon platform and across other websites. This service encompasses various types of advertisements, including Sponsored Products, Sponsored Brands, and Sponsored Display ads, each aimed at enhancing visibility and driving sales for sellers' products.

The platform allows for diverse advertising solutions that incorporate different budget allocations tailored to various ad types. Advertisers can utilize pay-per-click strategies to maximize their reach and effectiveness. Additionally, Amazon Ads employs data collection methods to track ad performance, leveraging various reporting APIs to provide insights into advertising metrics. 

By integrating with tools such as Data Keeper, Amazon Ads supports marketing data collection, helping businesses refine their advertising strategies. In summary, Amazon Ads offers a comprehensive suite of advertising solutions to help sellers effectively market their products in a competitive online marketplace.&lt;SEP&gt;Amazon Ads represents the advertising services offered by Amazon for promoting products within its marketplace.&lt;SEP&gt;Amazon Ads are advertising expenditures directly linked to specific brand advertising profiles.&lt;SEP&gt;Amazon Ads is another advertising platform that is run alongside Meta Ads within the same context.&lt;SEP&gt;Amazon Ads are advertising services offered by Amazon that began to have data availability from December 2025 onward.&lt;SEP&gt;Amazon Ads is a marketing platform where campaign performance is analyzed and reported as part of the weekly metrics.</data>
