<node id="ACOS">
  <data key="d0">ACOS</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">ACOS (Advertising Cost of Sales) is a metric used to evaluate the efficiency of advertising costs compared to sales.&lt;SEP&gt;ACOS (Advertising Cost of Sales) is a key performance metric used to evaluate the cost-effectiveness of advertising spend relative to revenue generated.&lt;SEP&gt;ACOS, or Advertising Cost of Sales, is a metric that tracks the ratio of advertising spend to sales, used to evaluate campaign profitability.&lt;SEP&gt;ACOS (Advertising Cost of Sales) is a metric used to assess the efficiency of advertising campaigns.&lt;SEP&gt;ACOS (Advertising Cost of Sales) is calculated as cost divided by sales multiplied by 100, serving as an inverse relationship to ROAS for verification.&lt;SEP&gt;ACOS (Advertising Cost of Sales) measures the cost of advertising relative to sales.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cf1c928d713e5e851131e4dc6014a04e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-beb0a5fe192f87168f3bd926721264cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-deb6c473ba9d1e163a8254ec0cc102e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b69eda95423abf15f65e2b09388f5e12&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1404c32ad3ac92f1335a8a727b19187f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a87eee8ac11fd894680cc50e6addb730</data>
