<node id="CTR">
  <data key="d0">CTR</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">CTR, or Click-Through Rate, is a key performance metric used in online advertising to assess the effectiveness of advertisements. It quantifies the ratio of users who click on an ad compared to the total number of users who view that ad. Specifically, CTR is calculated by dividing the number of clicks by the number of impressions (views) and then multiplying the result by 100 to express it as a percentage.

This metric serves as an essential indicator of an ad's performance, revealing how well it engages users. By measuring the percentage of clicks relative to impressions, CTR provides insights into the effectiveness of an advertising campaign, allowing marketers to evaluate and optimize their strategies. 

In summary, CTR is crucial for understanding user interaction with advertisements, as it highlights the proportion of viewers who take action by clicking on the ad.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-beb0a5fe192f87168f3bd926721264cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-deb6c473ba9d1e163a8254ec0cc102e8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d1e9d390a18c25c6c9a57186d9e94536&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58d7e8a116fefa67e3e7f52d7f4a2cf9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e34ee2fcd7694b11689017ca396f40d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1404c32ad3ac92f1335a8a727b19187f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a87eee8ac11fd894680cc50e6addb730&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1e60131ff9e1a54afbb27933fca77f0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-308fbcd2551064ebc587e520ff4a9ace</data>
