  <data key="d5">1775315610</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CPC">
  <data key="d0">CPC</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">CPC, or Cost Per Click, is a widely recognized pricing model utilized in online advertising that specifies the amount an advertiser pays for each click on their advertisement. This model is particularly significant as it allows advertisers to gauge the effectiveness of their ads based on the actual engagement they receive. The cost associated with CPC can vary based on multiple factors, including the advertising platform, the ad’s context, and the competitive landscape for relevant keywords.

As a digital advertising measurement, CPC serves as a critical market price signal, indicating the financial commitment made by companies each time a user clicks on their ad. This metric is standardized and functions as a key performance indicator, reflecting how much money is spent for individual clicks. Advertisers often rely on CPC to manage their budgets and assess the return on investment for their advertising campaigns.

In summary, CPC encapsulates a crucial aspect of digital marketing, representing both a payment model and a measurement tool that plays an essential role in the planning and execution of advertising strategies across various platforms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-beb0a5fe192f87168f3bd926721264cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d1e9d390a18c25c6c9a57186d9e94536&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-58d7e8a116fefa67e3e7f52d7f4a2cf9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f1399e1cbd030ecd0b96943f50c69ab0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ddbf21ec7f47d630ad746086b6682fc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26c52c954d001b7f51d6f34c24f651ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7e34ee2fcd7694b11689017ca396f40d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-710148053302ca20be85cbe92ab8f074&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a87eee8ac11fd894680cc50e6addb730&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-308fbcd2551064ebc587e520ff4a9ace</data>
