<node id="Cost Cap">
  <data key="d0">Cost Cap</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Cost Cap is a bidding strategy aimed at maintaining cost predictability by setting a cap at 1.2x to 1.5x the target CPA.&lt;SEP&gt;Cost Cap refers to the monetary limit set for a campaign, which should not fall below a specified multiple of the historical Cost Per Acquisition (CPA).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-ba6de65dea0c52394963037230c64351&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5f8083e1466c400ead556f945e1c01b3</data>
