<node id="Learning Phase">
  <data key="d0">Learning Phase</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Learning Phase refers to the period required for ad platforms to gather enough conversion data to optimize performance effectively.&lt;SEP&gt;Learning Phase refers to the period during which an ad set is optimizing its performance based on interactions.&lt;SEP&gt;The learning phase is a period when ad sets are assessed to optimize delivery and performance outcomes.&lt;SEP&gt;The Learning Phase refers to the period when the delivery system investigates effective ways to present a new or revised ad set.&lt;SEP&gt;The Learning Phase is a period for new or significantly edited ad sets characterized by performance volatility and resets upon major changes.&lt;SEP&gt;The learning phase is a period for newly edited ad sets during which performance can be unstable until sufficient results are obtained.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-abc482d1d7accb22469a33ba2864c773&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26c52c954d001b7f51d6f34c24f651ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e746e7fef455022aa3084cbaa54d7d3f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a910f1c6110c32f3b28e6e69b0371ada&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b70dcbf46893fec74c116376cce3d4cf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a84cf461c30eed0176d01b34c9ddcfab</data>
