<node id="Audit Report">
  <data key="d0">Audit Report</data>
  <data key="d1">report</data>
  <data key="d2">The Audit Report is a comprehensive document designed to present findings and conclusions regarding a financial review, highlighting the status of the audited entity as PASS, WARN, or FAIL. It is structured to summarize the audit results, findings, and suggested corrections derived from a thorough financial analysis. The report serves as a documented assessment that evaluates the financial practices and compliance of an organization.

Additionally, the Audit Report reflects the independent validation efforts conducted by the auditor, particularly assessing the outputs associated with specific scripts or coding tools, such as the `setup_n8n_delivery_email.py` and `tools/data_keeper.py`. These validations focus on various critical areas, including functionality, data integrity, and code quality. The report not only includes scores related to these evaluations but also identifies issues and provides detailed comments, which are essential for guiding the Chief Financial Officer (CFO) in decision-making processes.

Overall, the Audit Report serves as an invaluable resource for ensuring financial accuracy and compliance, while also offering insights into specific technical implementations within the organization.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-76164881663597e7f60e0b9203320ac3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bcdebc0475d4243fd4d254986b49391c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-834ba5f6dae18383c4ff63198c6f5143&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a2a416ce8319befb6569970717351ac6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a53e9337bdf20e7f3e970fd6d648713e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d06f425bac82c61d59416b2891c27c80&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d46bf96e549f6cf9637bba620110856c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed4beb9de386e201fd48d2d662de35eb</data>
