<node id="Period Consistency">
  <data key="d0">Period Consistency</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Period Consistency ensures that all tables utilize the same date range for comparisons during the auditing process.&lt;SEP&gt;Period Consistency involves ensuring that all revenue tables use the same timeframe, which is critical for accurate reporting.&lt;SEP&gt;Period Consistency involves ensuring all data calculations are performed within the same date range, noted for critical issues in the audit.&lt;SEP&gt;Period Consistency is a logical check to ensure all financial tables refer to the same time periods; however, it currently allows for potential mismatches.</data>
