<node id="KPI">
  <data key="d0">KPI</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">KPI (Key Performance Indicator) refers to measurable values that demonstrate how effectively a company is achieving key business objectives.&lt;SEP&gt;KPI refers to Key Performance Indicators used for monitoring performance in various aspects of a business.&lt;SEP&gt;KPI stands for Key Performance Indicator, which measures the performance of different product lines in relation to content views and sales trends.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0c92907c88b291f8936e3298a0588985&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-565e3686182be6732f4eb713f7aefecc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5d3c100505b7a39487d366a975efa893</data>
