<node id="Breakdown Effect">
  <data key="d0">Breakdown Effect</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Breakdown Effect is a framework used to interpret findings and explain decision-making processes within a system.&lt;SEP&gt;The Breakdown Effect describes the phenomenon where ad systems may stop functioning optimally due to various underlying issues.&lt;SEP&gt;The Breakdown Effect refers to the misinterpretation that Meta's system reallocates budget to underperforming segments, while the system actually optimizes for marginal efficiency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-26c52c954d001b7f51d6f34c24f651ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3cdc64d5c67bc92f881811763dfbc07d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-598aca3d6f829fff536ed40059c3b236</data>
