<node id="Airtable Base">
  <data key="d0">Airtable Base</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Airtable base is a dataset reference that may be used within a workflow environment for managing task information.&lt;SEP&gt;Airtable Base refers to the database environment used for managing data related to workflows in both PROD and WJ TEST environments.&lt;SEP&gt;The Airtable Base refers to the structured database in Airtable that contains various tables and records.&lt;SEP&gt;The Airtable base is used for managing records in the context of the n8n workflows, highlighting the transition from one base to another.</data>
