<node id="Webhook">
  <data key="d0">Webhook</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Webhook refers to a method of augmenting or altering the behavior of a web application with custom callbacks.&lt;SEP&gt;Webhook is a mechanism that allows one application to send real-time data to another whenever an event occurs, which is a focal point in troubleshooting n8n server issues.&lt;SEP&gt;Webhook is a method of sending data to a server through a specified URL, utilized in the n8n automation process.&lt;SEP&gt;Webhook refers to an automated message sent from n8n to Shopify, triggering actions based on specific events during the survey process.&lt;SEP&gt;Webhook is a method for sending real-time data notifications and integrations via HTTP requests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8a9bba4946f1d11c925c1405111249f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-91bdba8d279e91794bda27ec40d1bbd1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7fa81dc7d19a7c2d0fbd95c643e718fa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ebe22097b3fe7a799c85ef9b2aac8f2e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-5b6524cd2c19195670c840d97ba6eda0</data>
