<node id="Amazon PPC Executor Workflow">
  <data key="d0">Amazon PPC Executor Workflow</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Amazon PPC Executor Workflow describes an automated process for optimizing PPC campaigns for Fleeters Inc, incorporating human approval and specific budget rules.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-115f5f6888d3e784ce289c50787ec500</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_executor.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315195</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Proposals">
  <data key="d0">Proposals</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">Proposals are generated based on campaign analysis to suggest bid, budget, and action adjustments for approval.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-115f5f6888d3e784ce289c50787ec500</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_executor.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315196</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PPC Change Log">
  <data key="d0">PPC Change Log</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">The PPC Change Log records all actions taken during the PPC optimization process, including executed changes and timestamps.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-115f5f6888d3e784ce289c50787ec500</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_executor.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315196</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PPC Executor">
  <data key="d0">PPC Executor</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The PPC Executor refers to the automated process implemented to execute proposed changes in campaign settings based on human approval.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-115f5f6888d3e784ce289c50787ec500</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_executor.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Keyword Harvesting">
  <data key="d0">Keyword Harvesting</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Keyword Harvesting is a procedure used to identify profitable search terms for inclusion in PPC campaigns based on specific criteria.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-115f5f6888d3e784ce289c50787ec500</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_executor.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Keyword Bid Adjustments">
  <data key="d0">Keyword Bid Adjustments</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Keyword Bid Adjustments are rules applied to modify bids based on the performance of keywords within campaigns.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-115f5f6888d3e784ce289c50787ec500</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_executor.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315197</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Keyword-Level Proposals">
  <data key="d0">Keyword-Level Proposals</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-115f5f6888d3e784ce289c50787ec500</data>
  <data key="d2">Keyword Bid Adjustments are included in Keyword-Level Proposals to optimize the bidding strategy based on keyword performance.</data>
  <data key="d1">UNKNOWN</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_executor.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315203</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Attribution Window">
  <data key="d0">Attribution Window</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">Attribution window is a measurement period for tracking sales and views, commonly set to 14 days for clicks and 1 day for views.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1404c32ad3ac92f1335a8a727b19187f</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_tester.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315210</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="PROFILE_BRAND_MAP">
  <data key="d0">PROFILE_BRAND_MAP</data>
  <data key="d1">data</data>
  <data key="d2">PROFILE_BRAND_MAP is a data structure that maps brand names to their identifiers, such as "GROSMIMI USA" to "Grosmimi".</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1404c32ad3ac92f1335a8a727b19187f</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_tester.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315210</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Amazon PPC Tester">
  <data key="d0">Amazon PPC Tester</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Amazon PPC Tester is a tool used for validating and analyzing advertising campaigns on the Amazon platform.&lt;SEP&gt;Amazon PPC Tester is a role responsible for validating the accuracy of daily analysis flows for Amazon PPC advertising.&lt;SEP&gt;Amazon PPC Tester specializes in purchase intent search metrics, including ACOS and various ad types (SP/SB/SD).</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1404c32ad3ac92f1335a8a727b19187f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a87eee8ac11fd894680cc50e6addb730&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f1c07b09e4855e6a32993ae664eb166</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_tester.md&lt;SEP&gt;workflow__google_ads_tester.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775317522</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Campaign Name Parsing">
  <data key="d0">Campaign Name Parsing</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Campaign name parsing involves analyzing and organizing campaign data but is not part of the classification based on Profile ID.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1404c32ad3ac92f1335a8a727b19187f</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_tester.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315211</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Amazon PPC Tester Command">
  <data key="d0">Amazon PPC Tester Command</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Amazon PPC Tester Command is a command-line interface for executing various functions of the Amazon PPC Tester tool.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1404c32ad3ac92f1335a8a727b19187f</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_tester.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Amazon PPC Daily Analysis Flow">
  <data key="d0">Amazon PPC Daily Analysis Flow</data>
  <data key="d1">concept</data>
  <data key="d2">The Amazon PPC Daily Analysis Flow encompasses data collection, metric calculation, and report generation for Amazon PPC campaigns.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a87eee8ac11fd894680cc50e6addb730</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_tester.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775315212</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Meta Tester">
  <data key="d0">Meta Tester</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Meta Tester refers to the role focused on validating performance metrics for Facebook and Instagram ads based on exposure.&lt;SEP&gt;Meta Tester is a validation agent that verifies the accuracy of Meta Ads daily analysis flow.&lt;SEP&gt;Meta Tester focuses on metrics based on impressions and social media, utilizing CPM and Frequency.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a87eee8ac11fd894680cc50e6addb730&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-60333fb05f4e2e3fdfe5f70765228ad5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7f1c07b09e4855e6a32993ae664eb166</data>
  <data key="d4">workflow__amazon_ppc_tester.md&lt;SEP&gt;workflow__meta_tester.md&lt;SEP&gt;workflow__google_ads_tester.md</data>
  <data key="d5">1775317521</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Payload Structure">
